t: O*p come, let us sing unto the Lord:*s let us make a joyful noise to the rock of our salvation.
Let*p us come before his presence with thanksgiving, and make a joyful noise unto him with psalms.
For*p the Lord*s is a great God, and a great King above all gods.
In*p his hand are the deep places of the earth: the strength of the hills is his also.
The*p sea is his, and he made it: and his hands formed the dry land.
O*p come, let us worship and bow down: let us kneel before the Lord*s our maker.
For*p he is our God; and we are the people of his pasture, and the sheep of his hand. To day if ye will hear his voice,
Harden*p not your heart, as in the provocation, and as in the day of temptation in the wilderness:
When*p your fathers tempted me, proved me, and saw my work.
Forty*p years long was I grieved with this generation, and said, It is a people that do err in their heart, and they have not known my ways:
Unto*p whom I sware in my wrath that they should not enter into my rest.
